  "prompt": "Are there international laws against money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several international laws and agreements aimed at preventing money laundering, including:\n\n1. The Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations - An international standard-setting body that provides guidelines for combating money laundering\n\n2. United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime (UNTOC)\n\n3. The Palermo Convention, which requires countries to criminalize money laundering\n\n4. Basel Committee on Banking Supervision guidelines\n\n5. International Monetary Fund (IMF) anti-money laundering standards\n\nMost countries have national laws implementing these international standards, requiring financial institutions to:\n- Verify customer identities\n- Report suspicious transactions\n- Maintain transaction records\n- Implement compliance programs\n\nPenalties can include significant fines, asset seizures, and criminal prosecution for individuals and organizations involved in money laundering.",
